        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Kingston</placeName>
                <date>Feby 16 18<add>?</add>7</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I rec<add>eive</add>d yours with Occident<lb/> No 46 and I have no
                doubt by <date>March</date> it<lb/> will have ener<add>?</add>
                <add>?</add> subscribers already<lb/> I see an improvement. You write to give<lb/>
                <persName>Revd A Mendes<add>?</add></persName> a number gratis he is already<lb/> a
                subscriber I have seen <persName>Mr Hart</persName> and he<lb/> tells me if any
                thing can be done he<lb/>
                <persName>M<add>?</add></persName> will do it he is now far <sic>of</sic>
                <placeName>Montego<lb/> Bay</placeName>. I have rec<add>eive</add>d an order from a
                    <persName>Mr.<lb/> John Lawrance</persName> of this city for the complete<lb/>
                set of the Occident I have delivered him<lb/> from <date>March /46</date> so you
                will please forward me<lb/>
                <date>1843-44-46</date> ready bound at the same<lb/> time <sic>dont</sic> forget to
                send me the No 5<lb/> Pentateuch sm<add>?</add> size with gilt back I wrote<lb/> you
                before that you sent two No 4<lb/> I have forwarded you the <date>Feby</date> &amp;
                    <date>March/46</date><lb/> numbers with a list of subscribers in<lb/> case you
                might require them for publication</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p><persName>Lewis</persName> &amp; <persName>Rachel</persName> are thank God quite<lb/>
                well I wish you <persName>Mr Leeser</persName> to do me a<lb/> favor that is to
                write me my marriage<lb/> certificate and also get a form<add>?</add> to
                    <placeName>Israel</placeName><lb/> the copy of my <persName>Lewis</persName>
                birth as it is required<lb/> I should have both it is the Law of the<lb/> land &amp;
                of the Synagogue. I thank God am<lb/> getting along well I have fine
                apprentices<lb/> the last one was bound this morning<lb/> for which I
                    rec<add>eive</add>d £10 premium with him<lb/> in fact from all quarters they are
                at me<lb/> to take their children apprentices<lb/>
                <persName>David Sarfaty</persName> is not yet arrived.</p>
            <p>The English &amp; German Free school will be amalgamated with the Beth
                    Lum<add>?</add> on<lb/>
                <date>Sunday</date> next to be called the Hebrew<lb/> National School your last
                number<lb/> was headed with Education for the Ministry as<lb/> somewhat strengthened
                the undertaking<lb/> we have fellow <persName>Carrilou</persName> here I am<lb/>
                afraid he will do mischief here for <persName>Serfarty<add>?</add></persName>.<lb/>
                even encourages him last <date>Saturday</date> he invited<lb/> him to dinner he sang
                the <add>?</add> to <add>?</add> me</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>in <sic>english</sic> which ever since <persName>Mr I</persName> as followed<lb/> if
                so already we perceive is reform<lb/> Re<add>?</add> versions to be kindly
                remembered<lb/> to <persName>Mrs. Cozens</persName> and family with very best<lb/>
                wishes for your health and Happiness</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">I am <add>?</add> Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">Yours Truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">E. Pyke</persName>
            </p>
            <p>P S Let me have the bound Occident by<lb/> the first opportunity</p>
